            {
               "text": "### Images from Athens\n\nThese images are copyright for Athens and allowed to be used according to the license determined by them.\n\nTo visualize all images, use the left and right arrows on the slide below.",
               "source": null,
               "date_time": null,
               "isTable": false,
               "imgdesc": "",
               "format": "markdown",
               "PostMention": ""
            },
            {
               "text": "<p><div class=\"htSlides\"><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">1 / 3</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"imgAthens\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('imgAthens', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Erechtheion temples in Athens, Greece (<htcite0>). Photo taken on <htdate0>, during a visit to the site.</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>Culture and Civilization (<a href=\"index.html?page=history\" onclick=\"htLoadPage('history','html', '', false); return false;\">History</a>)</li></ul></div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">2 / 3</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"img5\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img5', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Columns present at the Parthenon, Greece. Photo taken on <htdate0>, during a visit to the archaeological site.</div></div><div class=\"htSlide\"><div class=\"htSlideCounter\">3 / 3</div><img class=\"imgGameSize\" id=\"img0\" onclick=\"htImageZoom('img0', '0%')\"><div class=\"htSlideCaption\">Map of the \"world\" © Trustees of the British Museum (<htcite1>). Shared under the <a href=\"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by-nc/4.0/\" target=\"_blank\">Creative Commons Attribution-NonCommercial-ShareAlike 4.0 International (CC BY-NC-SA 4.0)</a>.</div><div class=\"htSlideRefs\"><b>Related content:</b><ul><li>Comparing Worlds (<a href=\"index.html?page=atlas\" onclick=\"htLoadPage('atlas','html', '', false); return false;\">Atlas</a>)</li><li>The Ancient Babylonian World Map (<a href=\"index.html?page=atlas\" onclick=\"htLoadPage('atlas','html', '', false); return false;\">Atlas</a>)</li><li>Cradles of civilization (Part I) (<a href=\"index.html?page=history\" onclick=\"htLoadPage('history','html', '', false); return false;\">History</a>)</li><li>Anachronism (<a href=\"index.html?page=literature\" onclick=\"htLoadPage('literature','html', '', false); return false;\">Understanding Texts</a>)</li><li>Equality Levels (<a href=\"index.html?page=literature\" onclick=\"htLoadPage('literature','html', '', false); return false;\">Understanding Texts</a>)</li><li>Did texts written in Mesopotamia describe the world we know today? (<a href=\"index.html?page=myths_believes\" onclick=\"htLoadPage('myths_believes','html', '', false); return false;\">Myths and Believes</a>)</li><li>Has there never been a flood? (<a href=\"index.html?page=myths_believes\" onclick=\"htLoadPage('myths_believes','html', '', false); return false;\">Myths and Believes</a>)</li></ul></div></div><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-left htSlidePrev\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(-1);\"></i><i class=\"fa-solid fa-chevron-right htSlideNext\" onclick=\"htPlusDivs(1);\"></i></div></p>",
